{
  "stem": "15577.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was established in March '43.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And all the Jews--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'41-- excuse me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, '43 we have been to [INAUDIBLE] to the camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In '41, they came in order, and they gave us I think two weeks or something like this.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All the Jews of Crakow have to move into a closed area, which was-- it was even not the so-called Crakow ghetto from before the war.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Crakow ghetto from before there war was a place where most of the Jews were living, especially these religious Jews.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It wasn't close at that time, but it was called a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it wasn't the same place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was Crakow-- there's a-- the biggest river of Poland is also passing through the Crakow and divides Crakow in two parts.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we have to go to the other part of the river, which is called Podgorze.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was established the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In the-- in the very beginning the ghetto was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] quite big.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We moved in, then the fences and the stone fence and other fences weren't even ready.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they were still building them or putting them and it depends, but mostly everybody got one-room apart-- a one-room apartment.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There were no one-room apartments, so we have to-- to be with another family or two families, depends.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The Jewish community was-- was-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Jewish community was giving the apartments to the-- to the people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "After a short time, the ghetto was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they made it-- they-- they-- closed, I think, a set part of it and threw out all the Jews from there and packed them together.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish-- like-- like Jewish Federation here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the Jewish leadership, established by the-- by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
